Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.38,0:00:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know there's an awesome\Ntreasure at the end of this sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.61,0:00:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever gets it can be King\Nof the Pirates! Isn't that exciting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.18,0:00:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unheard-of adventures are waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.39,0:00:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage! Let that shred of courage grow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.26,0:00:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.90,0:00:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The horizons everyone\Ndreamed of were separate at first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.68,0:00:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they can be seen\Nthrough a single telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.82,0:00:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter compass of destiny\Nis leading your heart astray
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.16,0:00:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so turn the wheel in the other direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.06,0:01:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.13,0:01:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss aside your bonds and your past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can surely smile despite that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears shed trying to achieve\Nyour dreams aren't for naught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precious in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commodore seems sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.24,0:01:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Just after he made such a\Ngreat friend all the way out here...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.15,0:01:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of this makes any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.65,0:01:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We set sail first thing tomorrow morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.49,0:01:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the villagers are so\Nbloodthirsty we can't go near 'em,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.29,0:02:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not to mention, the bell\Ndidn't ring again today...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.16,0:02:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't show your face around me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.17,0:02:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want your wife to end up a widow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.38,0:02:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Eternal Friends! The Vowed Bell\NEchoes Across the Mighty Seas!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.69,0:02:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a heartrending way to leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.50,0:02:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.21,0:02:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.71,0:02:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.38,0:02:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.62,0:03:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Botanist, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.69,0:03:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.93,0:03:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If these are the victims\Nof your "advancements,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.20,0:03:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then we should never have accepted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kindred Trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.24,0:03:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is said that all the spirits of our\Nancestors who died on this island
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are guided to them by the bell\Nso they can settle inside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.32,0:03:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of our ancestors who lived on\Nthe island since the age of Shandora
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.66,0:03:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,watch over us from those sacred, white trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kindred Woods are so\Ntruly important to us Shandians
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:04:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we've protected them as much\Nas we've protected our own lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we chopped them all down...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.05,0:04:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The warriors were angry and\Ninstantly took up their weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--We must drive them off this island!\N--Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.63,0:04:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but since you had saved so\Nmany of the villagers' lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that attitude was\Nanger they couldn't act on...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.71,0:04:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was just for tree research...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers' anger won't go away now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I thought I would at least ask why...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.39,0:04:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...before you left...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Someone help with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Trees where ancestors' spirits dwell...\N--Get it all on board now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea. We've done something\Nthat can never be taken back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers are right to be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Commodore! We had no choice, given--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No excuses! I only did what satisfied me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.48,0:05:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that aside from\Nproclaiming the city's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that bell also served to guide\Ntheir ancestors' spirits to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we cut down those trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.93,0:05:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no reason to be forgiven!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.63,0:05:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.44,0:05:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.51,0:05:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Leave all the gold behind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.65,0:05:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland and his men are preparing to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.43,0:06:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse! Where were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.34,0:06:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.17,0:06:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if you knew a single, important\Ntree was tainted by poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that its poison would\Neventually spread into the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.95,0:06:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,affect people, and kill an island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.16,0:06:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if you knew beforehand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What are you talking about?!\N--What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was us...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.06,0:06:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would we do with\Nthat single, important tree?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Go quickly and stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.64,0:06:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool! You know what they've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.45,0:06:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we part now, we'll regret it\Nfor the rest of our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.75,0:06:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You finally made such a dear friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we Shandians owe them so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're going to leave them\Nhurt for the rest of their lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.12,0:07:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll probably sound like an excuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for the commodore's honor, I must say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.77,0:07:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those woods of yours were already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.27,0:07:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The true horror of the Kinetsu plague\Nis that it can also infect plant life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.65,0:07:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because he knew this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.88,0:07:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the commodore pleaded with\Nyou without regard for his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.12,0:07:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From people to forest, forest to people...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.89,0:07:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Several small islands have been\Ndestroyed in exactly that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's nothing to worry about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.53,0:07:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We finished checking\Nthe entire forest yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that we cut\Ndown your beloved woods
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without knowing or explaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.14,0:07:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd probably still be unforgivable\Neven with an explanation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but a botanist would never harm\Na forest without good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commodore doesn't hate\Ngods and spirits and stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that he always\Nknows what's most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.46,0:08:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means... they did it for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.54,0:08:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.74,0:08:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone have everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All except one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.25,0:08:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit mopin'! Just forget about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.89,0:08:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! It's time to go!\NEveryone to your positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.96,0:08:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're now heading back\Nto the Lvneel Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've committed such a sin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.04,0:09:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.95,0:09:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the bell ringing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Noland-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.10,0:09:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Louder! So Noland and the others can hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.87,0:09:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.64,0:10:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.18,0:10:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep on ringing the bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.48,0:10:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that your ship won't get\Nlost at sea when you return...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.39,0:10:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that you won't lose sight\Nof this island during a storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.59,0:10:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ring this bell and wait for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.17,0:10:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet again someday\Nfor sure! Friend of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.88,0:10:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can... come back again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.49,0:10:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll be back! I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.67,0:11:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet again someday for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.42,0:11:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There once was a man\Nnamed Montblanc Noland,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.76,0:11:29.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"North Blue-- Lvneel Kingdom"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.36,0:11:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from a kingdom in the northern seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.33,0:11:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland the Explorer always told\Nstories of incredible adventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.97,0:11:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the villagers could never\Ntell if they were true or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.94,0:11:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, Noland returned from a\Njourney and reported to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stands all the more\Nproudly and beautifully in ruin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.82,0:12:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This city is named Shandora! The term\N"city of gold" fits it like none other!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:03.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Five Years Later"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marie Jois has finally granted us\Npermission to enter the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.43,0:12:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, I wish to send\Nyou on another mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.67,0:12:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it would be my pleasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I've decided my soldiers will\Njoin you on this journey, as will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Understood?\N--Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:25.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"One Year Before Noland's Arrival"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Calgara!\N--Seto...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.95,0:12:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're off to ring the bell, right? I'll help!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Nola. You've sure settled into these ruins!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.07,0:12:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! When do you suppose\NNoland-san and the others will come?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.61,0:12:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you ever ask when you come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.94,0:12:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be so easy for him to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.01,0:12:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was born in the far northern seas.\NHe also has a family back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.82,0:13:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he did promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.19,0:13:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we keep ringing this\Nbell here, he'll show up sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.80,0:13:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?! This looks bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.83,0:13:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Seto! We have to protect the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.86,0:13:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.56,0:13:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does the island suddenly end here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.20,0:13:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you! You lied to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.01,0:13:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this gold of yours?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did the village go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.81,0:14:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to this island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.95,0:14:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara! If you're alive, let me hear it!\NThe sound of the gold bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.39,0:14:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, fire of Shandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.26,0:14:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland's public execution's about to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This way, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.04,0:14:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a giant city of gold on\Nthe Grand Line island of Jaya!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.31,0:14:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The city of gold does exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.44,0:14:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hear from one of your crewmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.15,0:14:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this man telling the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.08,0:14:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's an absolute lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Noland-san is a liar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.79,0:14:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then were all his stories fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's messed up! He lied to the\Nwhole kingdom and acted like a hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.96,0:14:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that witness?!\NHe's not part of our crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:14:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see Calgara and the others?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.44,0:15:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seize them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.81,0:15:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Men...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.25,0:15:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For his heinous lies, Montblanc\NNoland is hereby sentenced
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to death by beheading!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.09,0:15:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Liar!\N--He's a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The commodore'd never lie!\N--Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.03,0:15:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar! Liar! Liar! Liar!...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.32,0:16:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God! It's a giant island of Vearth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Did you hear that? The singing\Nvoice of this beautiful Vearth...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.60,0:16:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is truly the birth of holy land.\NThat is where I must live!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.84,0:16:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?! I can't breathe well!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.01,0:16:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is everyone all right?!\N--Pull yourselves together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Pull yourselves together!\N--Tend to the wounded! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.05,0:16:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara! Intruders!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:17:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby claim this Vearth as mine! I am God!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.06,0:17:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop them, warriors!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.07,0:17:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot let this land be taken away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.10,0:17:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We made a promise, Noland...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.07,0:17:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That we would meet again someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara... Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.45,0:17:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you return to Jaya, what will\Nyou think when you see we're gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a little longer! I'll let\Nyou know that "we are here"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.00,0:17:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have so much to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.73,0:17:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.90,0:17:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only concerned for your well-being...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet again on the\Nsame land someday, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Light the fire of Shandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.15,0:18:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Warrior Calgara continued to shout.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.62,0:18:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just once would've been enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.19,0:18:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For he believed the fire of Shandora\Nwould echo and let all know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.13,0:18:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We are here!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.50,0:18:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the bell never once rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.34,0:18:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was later told to our\Nvillage by sailors from the Blue Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.44,0:18:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland, to whom we owe so much,\Nhad such pride for our city
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.51,0:18:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he refused to deny Shandora's\Nexistence and died known as a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.69,0:18:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was already too late,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.36,0:18:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for Great Warrior Calgara had died\Nhonorably in battle here in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.40,0:18:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never being able to convey his message...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.07,0:18:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is Great Warrior Calgara's greatest regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it could still reach him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.27,0:19:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bell! If we rang it now,\Nwould its sound reach Noland?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.15,0:19:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.22,0:19:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are close to Heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.39,0:19:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wyper! We'll die if we don't escape now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.63,0:19:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.03,0:19:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wyper...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.73,0:19:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eneru...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gives you the right\Nto take everything away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.27,0:19:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the sky! God's domain!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.21,0:19:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is an eyesore!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people, the trees, the land!\NReturn to where you belong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let everything rain into the Blue Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.79,0:19:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.13,0:19:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel Island won't last much longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.70,0:19:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of injured people!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get them into boats, then give them first aid!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.73,0:19:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.07,0:20:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hurry, into the ocean!\N--Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.64,0:20:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get chills when I imagine that\Ngirl's speech being any later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.44,0:20:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's far above now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.19,0:20:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time until\Nhis ship reaches the top of the vine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.80,0:20:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it Eneru wants there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gold bell at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.51,0:20:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scurrying angels are like a\Nline of ants that's been disturbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to where you belong, Skypiea!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hole in the White-White Sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:21:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no need for good\Nold God's Shrine either!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.13,0:21:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor for the city of Shandora below it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.71,0:21:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is but one thing left\Nin this land that I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.55,0:21:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The golden grand belfry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.69,0:21:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two voices, at this final stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.16,0:21:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! How can he run so fast?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami! Be all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.46,0:21:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I won't let you have\Nthe golden bell, Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.17,0:21:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're feeling lonely, talk to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.68,0:21:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gaze at the heavens\Nas you wander about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.78,0:21:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the moon,\Nyou keep your gaze constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.66,0:22:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your deep reflection wanes\Nas you slowly disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.84,0:22:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay as you are, let those words guide you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.02,0:22:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream, you travelers who spend\Ncountless nights drifting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.10,0:22:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you may not be able to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.53,0:22:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will surely start moving forward again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.65,0:22:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then! Time for that eyesore\Nof an island to disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.88,0:23:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?! The clouds are changing shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.25,0:23:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you have your way, Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.52,0:23:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no stopping this Raigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.23,0:23:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to escape, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.89,0:23:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can just catch him...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.63,0:23:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.00,0:23:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Angel Island Obliterated!\NThe Horror of the Raigo's Advent!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.20,0:23:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
